   "source": [
    "# Channel Generation for Dual Mobility Scenarios in 5G and Beyond\n",
    "\n",
    "The 5G networks are designed to support scenrios where both transmitter and receiver are moving. Such scenarios are very common in device to device (D2D) and vehicle to everything (V2X) use-cases. The dual mobility results in dual Doppler primarily because of the relative motion between the two mobile devices. Ths tutorial demonstates, how wireless channel can be generated for such scerarios.\n",
    "\n",
    "The tutorial covers the following\n",
    "\n",
    "- [Import Libraries](#Import-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [Import Python Libraries](#Import-Python-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [Import 5G Libraries](#Import-5G-Libraries)\n",
    "- [Simulation Parameters](#Simulation-Parameters)\n",
    "- [Generate Antenna Array](#Generate-Antenna-Array)\n",
    "    - [Generate Transmit Arrays](#Generate-Transmit-Arrays)\n",
    "    - [Generate Receiver Arrays](#Generate-Receiver-Arrays)\n",
    "- [Generate the Routes](#Generate-the-Routes)\n",
    "    - [Generate the BS Routes](#Generate-the-BS-Routes)\n",
    "    - [Generate the UE Routes](#Generate-the-UE-Routes)\n",
    "- [Simulation Layout](#Simulation-Layout)\n",
    "- [Channel Parameters, Channel Coefficients and OFDM Channel](#Channel-Parameters,-Channel-Coefficients-and-OFDM-Channel)\n",
    "- [Variation in Channel Power across Time](#Variation-in-Channel-Power-across-Time)\n",
    "\n",
    "Lets start the tutorial.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    \n",
    "## Import Libraries\n",
    "### Import Python Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "009315bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"-1\"\n",
    "os.environ['TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL'] = '3' \n",
    "\n",
    "# %matplotlib widget\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as patches\n",
    "import matplotlib.animation as animation\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d48ef55f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Import 5G Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "aff252fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# importing necessary modules for simulating channel model\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../../../\")\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import NodeMobility\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import AntennaArrays\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import SimulationLayout"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aee53b13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "7ad22d5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulation Parameters\n",
    "propTerrain      = \"UMi\"         # Propagation Scenario or Terrain for BS-UE links\n",
    "carrierFrequency = 5.4*10**9     # carrier frequency in Hz\n",
    "nBSs             = 3             # number of BSs \n",
    "nUEs             = 10            # number of UEs \n",
    "nSnapShots       = 14            # number of SnapShots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "934c185a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Antenna Array\n",
    "\n",
    "### Generate Transmit Arrays\n",
    "\n",
    "The following steps describe the procedure to generate AntennaArrays Objects at a single carrier frequency both at Tx and Rx side:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Choose an omni directional dipole antenna for Rx, for which we have to pass the string \"OMNI\" while instantiating `AntennaArrays` class.\n",
    "\n",
    "* Pass `arrayStructure` of `[1,1,2,2,1]` meaning 1 panel in vertical direction, 1 panel in horizonatal direction, 2 antenna elements per column per panel, 2 columns per panel and 1 correspond to antenna element being single polarized. \n",
    "\n",
    "* For this antenna structure, the number of Rx antennas `Nr` to be 4.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "dbc3e5f9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes3D: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at UE side\n",
    "# antenna element type to be \"OMNI\"\n",
    "# with single panel and 4 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "bsAntArray = AntennaArrays(antennaType = \"3GPP_38.901\", \n",
    "                           centerFrequency = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "                           arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,2,2,1]))\n",
    "                            \n",
    "bsAntArray()\n",
    "\n",
    "# num of Rx antenna elements\n",
    "nt = bsAntArray.numAntennas\n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Rx antenna element \n",
    "bsAntArray.displayAntennaRadiationPattern()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a6f8be8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate Receiver Arrays"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "44b80148",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes3D: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at UE side\n",
    "# antenna element type to be \"OMNI\"\n",
    "# with single panel and 4 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "ueAntArray = AntennaArrays(antennaType = \"OMNI\", \n",
    "                           centerFrequency = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "                           arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,2,2,1]))\n",
    "                            \n",
    "ueAntArray()\n",
    "\n",
    "# num of Rx antenna elements\n",
    "nr = ueAntArray.numAntennas\n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Rx antenna element \n",
    "ueAntArray.displayAntennaRadiationPattern()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "16febf0f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate the Routes\n",
    "\n",
    "### Generate the BS Routes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "63fde39a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# NodeMobility parameters\n",
    "# assuming that all the BSs are static and all the UEs are mobile.\n",
    "# time values at each snapshot.\n",
    "\n",
    "snapshotInterval = 10**-3/14     # 5 second\n",
    "\n",
    "speed      = 0.833 # speed of the UE 3 Kmph\n",
    "radius     = 250   # 3 Kmph\n",
    "timeInst   = snapshotInterval*np.arange(nSnapShots, dtype=np.float32) \n",
    "\n",
    "typeOfMobility = \"vehicle\"\n",
    "numVehicles    = nBSs\n",
    "timeInstances  = timeInst\n",
    "option         = \"optionA\"\n",
    "laneWidth      = 10\n",
    "numLanes       = 2\n",
    "vehicledropType = \"random\"\n",
    "randomizeOrientations = False\n",
    "\n",
    "BSroute    = NodeMobility(typeOfMobility, numVehicles, timeInstances, option, \n",
    "                          laneWidth, numLanes, vehicledropType, randomizeOrientations)\n",
    "BSroute()\n",
    "BSroute.displayRoute()\n",
    "# ax.set_aspect(True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92b339c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate the UE Routes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "396851a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# NodeMobility parameters\n",
    "# assuming that all the BSs are static and all the UEs are mobile.\n",
    "# time values at each snapshot.\n",
    "\n",
    "snapshotInterval        = 10**-3/14     # 5 second\n",
    "\n",
    "speed      = 0.833 # speed of the UE 3 Kmph\n",
    "radius     = 250   # 3 Kmph\n",
    "timeInst   = snapshotInterval*np.arange(nSnapShots, dtype=np.float32) \n",
    "\n",
    "typeOfMobility = \"vehicle\"\n",
    "numVehicles    = nUEs\n",
    "timeInstances  = timeInst\n",
    "option         = \"optionA\"\n",
    "laneWidth      = 10\n",
    "numLanes       = 2\n",
    "vehicledropType = \"random\"\n",
    "randomizeOrientations = False\n",
    "\n",
    "UEroute    = NodeMobility(typeOfMobility, numVehicles, timeInstances, option, \n",
    "                          laneWidth, numLanes, vehicledropType, randomizeOrientations)\n",
    "UEroute()\n",
    "UEroute.displayRoute()\n",
    "# ax.set_aspect(True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2752ff7d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation Layout\n",
    "\n",
    "We define the simulation topology parametes:\n",
    "\n",
    " - ``ISD``: Inter Site Distance\n",
    " - ``minDist``: Minimum distance between transmitter and receiver.\n",
    " - ``bsHt``: BS heights \n",
    " - ``ueHt``: UE heights\n",
    " - ``topology``: Simulation Topology\n",
    " - ``nSectorsPerSite``: Number of Sectors Per Site\n",
    " \n",
    "Furthermore, users can access and update following parameters as per their requirements for channel using the handle simLayoutObj.x where x is:\n",
    "\n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated immendiately after object creation\n",
    "    - ``UEtracks``\n",
    "    - ``UELocations``\n",
    "    - ``ueOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``UEvelocityVector``\n",
    "    - ``BStracks``\n",
    "    - ``BSLocations``\n",
    "    - ``bsOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``BSvelocityVector``\n",
    "    \n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated after calling the object\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "25c2616c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "      enableSpatialConsistency: True\n",
      "               memoryEfficient: False\n",
      "enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor: True\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7fb96d21c390>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Layout Parameters\n",
    "isd             = 500         # inter site distance\n",
    "minDist         = 35          # min distance between each UE and BS \n",
    "ueHt            = 1.5         # UE height\n",
    "bsHt            = 35          # BS height\n",
    "topology        = \"Hexagonal\" # BS layout type\n",
    "nSectorsPerSite = 3           # number of sectors per site\n",
    "\n",
    "memoryEfficient                = False\n",
    "enableSpatialConsistencyLoS    = True\n",
    "enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor = True\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"      enableSpatialConsistency: \"+str(enableSpatialConsistencyLoS))    \n",
    "print(\"               memoryEfficient: \"+str(memoryEfficient))    \n",
    "print(\"enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor: \"+str(enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor))    \n",
    "\n",
    "# simulation layout object                                 \n",
    "simLayoutObj = SimulationLayout(numOfBS = nBSs, \n",
    "                                numOfUE = nUEs,\n",
    "                                heightOfBS = bsHt, \n",
    "                                heightOfUE = ueHt,\n",
    "                                ISD = isd, \n",
    "                                layoutType = topology, \n",
    "                                numOfSectorsPerSite = nSectorsPerSite,\n",
    "                                ueRoute = UEroute,\n",
    "                                bsRoute = BSroute,\n",
    "                                memoryEfficient = memoryEfficient,\n",
    "                                useInitueLocations= True,\n",
    "                                enableSpatialConsistencyLoS = enableSpatialConsistencyLoS, \n",
    "                                enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor = enableSpatialConsistencyIndoor) \n",
    "\n",
    "# Update UE location for motion over a circle centered around the BS location.\n",
    "simLayoutObj.UELocations = -simLayoutObj.UEtracks.mean(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "simLayoutObj(terrain = propTerrain,\n",
    "             carrierFreq = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "             ueAntennaArray = ueAntArray,\n",
    "             bsAntennaArray = bsAntArray,\n",
    "             forceLOS = False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# displaying the topology of simulation layout\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = simLayoutObj.display2DTopology()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.scatter(simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,0]+simLayoutObj.UEtracks[:,0,0], \n",
    "           simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,1]+simLayoutObj.UEtracks[:,0,1],  \n",
    "           color=\"k\", label = \"NLoS Instants\", zorder=-1)\n",
    "ax.scatter(simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,0]+simLayoutObj.UEtracks[simLayoutObj.linkState[:,0,3],0,0],\n",
    "           simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,1]+simLayoutObj.UEtracks[simLayoutObj.linkState[:,0,3],0,1],  \n",
    "           color=\"r\", label = \"LoS Instants\", zorder=-1)\n",
    "ax.scatter(simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,0],simLayoutObj.UELocations[0,1], color=\"b\", label = \"UE-InitialLocation\", zorder=-3)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"x-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"y-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Simulation Topology\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "# plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "16345c99",

   "source": [
    "## Channel Parameters,  Channel Coefficients and OFDM Channel\n",
    "\n",
    "The user can access the channel coefficents and other parameters using following handles:\n",
    "\n",
    "- LSPs/SSPs: paramGenObj.x where x is\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    - ``delaySpread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoA_LoS``, ``phiAoA_mn``, ``phiAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoA_LoS``, ``thetaAoA_mn``, ``thetaAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoD_LoS``, ``phiAoD_mn``, ``phiAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoD_LoS``, ``thetaAoD_mn``, ``thetaAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``xpr``\n",
    "    - ``pathloss``, ``pathDelay``, ``pathPower``\n",
    "    - ``shadowFading``\n",
    "    \n",
    "- Channel Co-efficeints: channel.x where x is\n",
    "    - ``coefficients`` \n",
    "    - ``delays``\n",
    "\n",
    "- Shape of OFDM Channel:\n",
    "    - `Hf` is of shape : ``(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, Nfft, number of Rx antennas, number of Tx antennas)``"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "788c6f70",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[Warning]: Pathloss model for UMi is defined only for BS height 'hBS' = 10! Ignoring for now but might results in unexpected behaviour!\n",
      "[Warning]: UE height 'hUE' cannot be less than 1.5! These values are forced to 1.5!\n",
      "[Warning]: Pathloss model for UMi is defined only for  2D distances 'd2D' between 10m and 5Km! Some distances are from outside this interval!\n",
      "Ignoring for now but might result in unexpected behaviour!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate SSPs/LSPs Parameters: \n",
    "paramGenObj = simLayoutObj.getParameterGenerator(memoryEfficient = True, \n",
    "                                                 enableSpatialConsistencyForLSPs = True, \n",
    "                                                 enableSpatialConsistencyForSSPs = True,\n",
    "                                                 enableSpatialConsistencyForInitialPhases = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate Channel Coefficeints and Delays: SSPs/LSPs\n",
    "channel = paramGenObj.getChannel(applyPathLoss = True)\n",
    "# Channel coefficients can be accessed using: channel.coefficients\n",
    "# Channel delays can be accessed using:       channel.delays\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate OFDM Channel\n",
    "Nfft = 1024\n",
    "Hf   = channel.ofdm(30*10**3, Nfft, simLayoutObj.carrierFrequency)"
   ]
  },

    "## Variation in Channel Power across Time\n",
    "\n",
    "* The following code snippets displays the variation of received power of a UE when moves on a circular track (centered around origin) starting from its `initial position`.\n",
    "* In the current simulation we have 3 BSs and 1 UE moving on a circular track starting from a random intitial position inside a hexagonal layout."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "d5c7ca20",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (10,4))\n",
    "power   = 10*np.log10(((np.abs(Hf)**2).sum(axis=0).sum(axis=2).sum(axis=2).sum(axis=2).sum(axis=2))/(nr*nt))\n",
    "colors  = np.array(['palegreen', 'crimson','royalblue'])\n",
    "ax.plot(timeInst*1000, power[:,0], colors[0], label = \"BS-0\")\n",
    "ax.plot(timeInst*1000, power[:,1], colors[1], label = \"BS-1\")\n",
    "ax.plot(timeInst*1000, power[:,2], colors[2], label = \"BS-2\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(timeInst*1000)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid()\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Time Instances (milli-second)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Received-Power (dB)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Received-Power Variation With Time', fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
